
Davis Democrats/Yolo County Democrats is a City Politics political organization.

The Davis Democratic Headquarters opened on March 11, 2012 to serve the Democratic Party of Yolo County through the November 2012 election. The headquarters welcomes all Democrats from Yolo County to become involved in the reelection of President Barack Obama, Senator Dianne Feinstein, Congressmember John Garamendi, State Senator Lois Wolk, Assemblymember Mariko Yamada, as well as support other Democratic Party endorsed candidates and campaigns. Community volunteers and students looking for internships are encouraged to visit the headquarters.

